headline.main: NETHERLAND WARSHIP CAPTURED WINNIPEG; London Says Status of Germans on French Ship Is Not Clear

lead_paragraph: LONDON, June 2 -- Further proof that ships of the Royal Netherland Navy were playing their part in helping the British Navy to police the seas was provided in a communique issued tonight relating to the capture of the French ship Winnipeg.
abstract: Netherlands Navy aid to Brit Navy shown by part played in ss capture
